Description of male : larger and stouter than female, allotype (
Fig. 7
) 1.74 mm long, 4.25 times as long as wide; cephalothorax as long as wide, pereonite 2 as long as pereonite 1 , pereonites 4 to 6 equal in length. No significant sexual dimorphism in any appendages, but antennule with three aesthetascs.
